sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091173
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct uses two hybrid promoters. pLsr/cI drives expression of the LuxI and Mnt genes. The promoter is designed to respond to repression by LsrR, which can be derepressed by phosphorylated AI-2, and to repression by lambda cI. pTet/Mnt drives expression of the LuxI and cI genes. It is designed for repression by the Tet repressor, which can be derepressed by aTc, and by the Mnt repressor. LuxI is a sythase that produces AI-1.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Todd Eckdahl

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from luxICDABEG operon terminator of Vibrio fischeri <genbank>AF170104</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Bidirectional transcriptional terminator consisting of a 22 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In the naturally-occuring sequence there is a mismatch in the stem of the stem loop. This can be corrected via an A->G mutation (at position 40 -- sequence coordinate/not MFOLD coordinate). The above sequence does not reflect this mutation (but the MFOLD image does). This terminator's location cannot be found using some inverted repeat detectors like PALINDROME because it is too short and contains a mismatch. This one was found with the help of Tom Knight. It lies between two coding regions that point towards eachother.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cI lam
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cI repressor from E. coli phage lambda (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the cI repressor based on cI repressor from bacteriophage lambda modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein. cI repressor binds to the cI regulator (BBa_R0051).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
References (unparsed) here:

A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000

Octamerization of CI repressor is needed for effective repression of PRM and efficient switching from lysogeny. Ian B. Dodd,1 Alison J. Perkins, Daniel Tsemitsidis, and J. Barry Egan , Genes and Development (Vol 15, No. 22) 3013-3022: 2001

References (unparsed) here:

A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators , Elowitz M.B. , Leibler S., Nature(403),335-38: 2000

Octamerization of CI repressor is needed for effective repression of PRM and efficient switching from lysogeny. Ian B. Dodd,1 Alison J. Perkins, Daniel Tsemitsidis, and J. Barry Egan , Genes and Development (Vol 15, No. 22) 3013-3022: 2001

BBa_C0051 cI repressor is based on the cI repressor from the Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LAA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr, Voichita Marinescu and Alexander D. Wissner-Gross

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091105
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part comes from the Mnt promoter and the TetR promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This promoter is a modified version of the Mnt promoter that is also responsive to TetR. The promoter should be repressed by Mnt repressor. It should also be repressed by TetR, and in the absence of Mnt repressor, should be induced by aTc.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Mnt repressor binds as a tetramer to two half-operator sites. Introduction of TetR binding sites between the Mnt promoter -10 sequence and the start site for transcription should allow for repression by TetR. Accordingly, the hybrid promoter was designed by 1) Remove all bases of mnt promoter 3??? to -10: gagtcgtattaattt will be replaced by tccctatcagtgata, and 2) truncate the second half of ptet -10 and mutate -35 so that it function to bind tetR (replace ttgaca with actgta), but is not a promoter, and 3) place the tetR1 and tetR2 binding sites 3??? to truncated mnt -10 sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Robert Cool

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091106
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The Missouri Western/Davidson team designed primers for LsrA and extracted the DNA from E. coli MG1655. The CI portion was pulled from the registry as part number R0051.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This hybrid promoter uses the LsrA promoter that is capable of being repressed by LsrR - induction can occur with phospho-AI-2. Binding sites for cI repressor also occur. As a result the promoter is off in the absence of AI-2 and on in the presence of AI-2, but always off in the presence of cI.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The promoter region for LsrA should remain unaltered while cI binding sites (OR1 and OR2) are introduced downstream. The OR2 sites with cI bound should not allow transcription. The cI binding sites have a natural 6 bp spacer between them. It would be desirable to position the cI binding sites immediately downstream of the -10 region of the LsrA promoter. However, experimental evidence for the transciption start (+1) appears to be lacking.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Gordon

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: luxI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Synthesizes 3OC6HSL, which binds to LuxR.

The lux cassette of V. fischeri contains a left and a right promoter. The right promoter gives weak constitutive expression of downstream genes.This expression is up-regulated by the action of the Lux repressor, LuxR. Two molecules of LuxR protein form a complex with two molecules the signalling compound HSL. This complex binds to a palindromic site on the promoter, increasing the rate of transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: An LVA tail (sequence: AANDENYALVA) was added to increase protein degradation. .
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mnt (s)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: mnt repressor (strong) from Salmonella phage P22 (+LVA)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
wild type dimeric repressor from enterobacteriophage p22 with dissociation constant of 2.5*10^-12.

sequence was translated with the E.Coli K12 codon usage table, and nucleotides 95-97 was changed from AAT to AAC to avoid the cut site GAATTC (94-99).

Identification of Functionally Important Residues in the DNA Binding Region of the MNT Repressor
Kendall, KL; Sauer, RT
The Journal of Biological Chemistry, 264(23):13706-13710, 1989
